      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Dangerous Minds 1995. Hollywood. $103.92. 99 minutes. Closed captioned. R.</p>
        <p>Michelle Pfeiffer may not make the likeliest ex-marine teaching English to tough inner-city youngsters, but there she is at the blackboard in tight jeans and black leather as LouAnne Johnson, the real-life teacher who wrote the book from which John N. Smith's film was adapted. In a star vehicle that stays on the well-traveled road of "Stand and Deliver" and other movies about teachers taming rebellious teen-agers, Ms. Pfeiffer cracks the whip as arrestingly as Catwoman over her rough but lovable students, who, Janet Maslin wrote in The New York Times, predictably knuckle under in "a story you could second-guess in your sleep."</p>
      </block>
